<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-42-0920 </DOCNO><TEXT>UK electricity prices are set to become among the most expensive in theworld as a result of the Government's privatisation plans, accordingto an annual survey of international electricity costs. This year's NationalUtility Services' (NUS) survey shows the UK second only to Germany inthe international electricity price league table, following price increasesaveraging 5.45% which moved the country up from fourth position, theonly upward movement of the 11 countries surveyed. The survey also showsthat generation of electricity by nuclear power is becoming less popularin an increasing number of countries.</TEXT></DOC>